com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class GetTrustScoreResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianResponse
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.GetTrustScoreResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class GetTrustScoreResponse
extends SiperianResponse
    Response to a GetTrustScoreRequest.

    The response contains a trust score (type float) of the column specified in the request corresponding to a specific record. The trust score is based on the trust settings of the Admin system. If a custom trust setting was specified in the request, the trust score will be based on the custom trust setting.

    Usage Example:

    The code below shows how to print out the trust score in a GetTrustScoreResponse:

    GetTrustScoreResponse response = (GetTrustScoreResponse)
    sipClient.process(request);
    System.out.println("trust score: "+response.getTrustScore()+");

    For more details, see GetTrustScoreRequest.

    See Also:
    GetTrustScoreRequest, TrustSetting, Serialized Form

    API Pair: GetTrustScoreRequest

    API Group: Data Steward
